    <h3>February 12th, 2025</h3>
    <h5>Formatting tweak</h5>
    <p>
        A few minor updates to display formatting. The biggest of these is that we now use the race name in more places, including
        the header of series results. Race description still shows up when clicking through. When testing this, it looks like the
        trade off of wider race score columns is worth it to get the extra info for the clubs that use race names.
    </p>
    <br />
    <h3>January 23rd, 2025</h3>
    <h5>Racing Rules of Sailing 2025-2028</h5>
    <p>
        In addition to some minor changes to a few scoring codes, RRS 2025-2028 also includes a change to how scoring
        penalties are calculated. A Scoring Penalty should now be rounded to a single decimal place, like other calculated scores.
        Previously, penalties were rounded to the nearest whole number. The default scoring system in SailScores has been updated
        to comply with the new rules. There are also base systems added for those who need to use the pre-2025 scoring systems.
    </p>
